@startuml victor369basu_Real-time-stock-market-prediction

actor User
participant "producer.js" as Producer
participant "Kafka" as Kafka
participant "consumer.js" as Consumer
participant "ml_consumer.js" as MLConsumer
participant "pre_process.js" as Preprocessor
participant "tf_model.js" as TFModel
database "MongoDB" as MongoDB
participant "tf_train.js" as Trainer
participant "tf_validate.js" as Validator
participant "server.js" as Server

User -> Server: Request model training/validation
Server -> Trainer: Initiate training
Trainer -> MongoDB: Fetch historical data
MongoDB --> Trainer: Return data
Trainer -> TFModel: Train model
TFModel --> Trainer: Return trained model
Trainer -> MongoDB: Save model weights

Server -> Validator: Initiate validation
Validator -> MongoDB: Fetch test data
MongoDB --> Validator: Return data
Validator -> TFModel: Load model
Validator -> TFModel: Validate model
Validator -> MongoDB: Store performance metrics

Producer -> Kafka: Stream stock data
Kafka --> Consumer: Consume data
Consumer -> MongoDB: Store data

Kafka --> MLConsumer: Consume data
MLConsumer -> Preprocessor: Preprocess data
Preprocessor --> MLConsumer: Return preprocessed data
MLConsumer -> TFModel: Load model
MLConsumer -> TFModel: Generate prediction
MLConsumer -> MongoDB: Log prediction

User -> Server: Request real-time prediction
Server -> MongoDB: Fetch latest prediction
MongoDB --> Server: Return prediction
Server --> User: Display prediction

@enduml